    <title>rss live bookmarks do not update after resume from hibernation</title>
    <description>
        <paragraph id="2">
            <sentence id="2.1">If I hibernate my system and then resume, RSS feeds do not update.</sentence>
            <sentence id="2.2">This is only seen with ff 3beta1 (ff2 worked fine).</sentence>
            <sentence id="2.3">"Reload live bookmark" does not help either.</sentence>
            <sentence id="2.4">This might have something to do with the system clock jumping forward to the correct time when the computer is resumed</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="4">
            <sentence id="4.1">Steps to Reproduce:</sentence>
            <sentence id="4.2">1 hibernate</sentence>
            <sentence id="4.3">2 resume</sentence>
            <sentence id="4.4">3 look at RSS live bookmark</sentence>
            <sentence id="4.5">Actual Results:</sentence>
            <sentence id="4.6">I get the "old" results (from before the hibernation) together with a "loading" indication as the first bookmark.</sentence>
            <sentence id="4.7">This does not go away</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="5">
            <sentence id="5.1">Expected Results:  
The bookmarks should update within a reasonable time (~ 1 minute)</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="6">
            <sentence id="6.1">I run a fedora core 8 distro, nothing special ...</sentence>
        </paragraph>
    </description>
